msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 26"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:0.5"
msgid "26. Cīvarasibbanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on sewing robes"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.61, pts-cs-bu-pc26.1, pts-vp-en.2.285, ms2V_575
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

#. VAR: āyasmā udāyī paṭṭo → udāyi paṭṭo (bj) | udāyi paṭṭho (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī paṭṭo hoti cīvarakammaṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Udāyī had become skilled in making robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.3"
msgid "Aññatarā bhikkhunī yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Just then a certain nun approached Udāyī"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.5"
msgid "“sādhu me, bhante, ayyo cīvaraṃ sibbatū”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, would you please sew me a robe?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: _Paṭibhānacittaṃ_. _Citta_ is here equivalent to Sanskrit _citra_, which means colorful, variegated, decorative, etc., and by extension it also means a picture or painting, which seems to be the intended meaning here. _Paṭibhāna_ means something like impromptu imagination. The commentary, [](Sp.4.804.29), specifies that it was a picture of a couple having sexual intercourse. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī tassā bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbitvā surattaṃ suparikammakataṃ katvā majjhe paṭibhānacittaṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā saṃharitvā nikkhipi."
msgstr "He then sewed a robe for that nun, making it beautiful and nicely dyed, and he drew a creative picture in the middle of it. He then folded it and put it aside."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.7"
msgid "Atha kho sā bhikkhunī yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Soon afterwards that nun went to Udāyī"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.8"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.9"
msgid "“kahaṃ taṃ, bhante, cīvaran”ti?"
msgstr "“Venerable, where’s the robe?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.286
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.10"
msgid "“Handa, bhagini, imaṃ cīvaraṃ yathāsaṃhaṭaṃ haritvā nikkhipitvā yadā bhikkhunisaṃgho ovādaṃ āgacchati tadā imaṃ cīvaraṃ pārupitvā bhikkhunisaṃghassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito āgacchā”ti."
msgstr "“Now, Sister, take this robe as it’s folded and put it aside. When the Order of nuns goes to the instruction, then put it on and follow right behind the other nuns.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.11"
msgid "Atha kho sā bhikkhunī taṃ cīvaraṃ yathāsaṃhaṭaṃ haritvā nikkhipitvā yadā bhikkhunisaṃgho ovādaṃ āgacchati tadā taṃ cīvaraṃ pārupitvā bhikkhunisaṃghassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito āgacchati."
msgstr "And that nun did just that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.12"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized her,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.13"
msgid "“yāva chinnikā imā bhikkhuniyo dhuttikā ahirikāyo, yatra hi nāma cīvare paṭibhānacittaṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How wanton these nuns are, how brazen and shameless, in that they draw creative pictures on their robes.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_576
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.14"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "And the nuns asked her,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.15"
msgid "“kassidaṃ kamman”ti?"
msgstr "“Who did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.16"
msgid "“Ayyassa udāyissā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Udāyī.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.17"
msgid "“Yepi te chinnakā dhuttakā ahirikā tesampi evarūpaṃ na sobheyya, kiṃ pana ayyassa udāyissā”ti."
msgstr "“This sort of work would not even make those who are wanton, brazen, and shameless look good, let alone Venerable Udāyī.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_577
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.18"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The nuns told the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.19"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.20"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.21"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī sew a robe for a nun?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.22"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.23"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.24"
msgid "“Ñātikā te, udāyi, aññātikā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is she a relative of yours?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.25"
msgid "“Aññātikā, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.26"
msgid "“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātikāya na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā pāsādikaṃ vā apāsādikaṃ vā."
msgstr "“Foolish man, a man and a woman who are not related don’t know what’s appropriate and what’s inappropriate in dealing with each other, what’s inspiring and what’s not."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.27"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbissasi."
msgstr "And still you sewed a robe for an unrelated nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.28"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.29"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_578
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:1.30"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbeyya vā sibbāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk sews a robe for an unrelated nun, or gets one sewn, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, pts-cs-bu-pc26.2.1, ms2V_579
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_580
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.6"
msgid "Aññātikā nāma"
msgstr "Unrelated:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.287
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.7"
msgid "mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddhā."
msgstr "anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_581
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.8"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "A nun:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.9"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "she has been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_582
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.10"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "A robe:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
# NOTE: The six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see [](Mv.8.3.1). 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.11"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ."
msgstr "one of the six kinds of robes."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, pts-vp-pli4.62, ms2V_583
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.12"
msgid "Sibbeyyāti"
msgstr "Sews:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.13"
msgid "sayaṃ sibbati ārāpathe ārāpathe āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he sews it himself, then for each stitch he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_584
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.14"
msgid "Sibbāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets sewn:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.15"
msgid "aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.1.16"
msgid "Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi sibbati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he only asks once, then even if the other sews many times, he commits one offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc26.2.2, ms2V_585
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.2.1"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he sews her a robe or gets one sewn, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.2.2"
msgid "Aññātikāya vematiko cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated, but he is unsure if she is, and he sews her a robe or gets one sewn, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.2.3"
msgid "Aññātikāya ñātikasaññī cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated, but he perceives her as related, and he sews her a robe or gets one sewn, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_586
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.2.4"
msgid "Ekatoupasampannāya cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he sews a robe, or gets one sewn, for a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.2.5"
msgid "Ñātikāya aññātikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is related, but he perceives her as unrelated, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.2.6"
msgid "Ñātikāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is related, but he is unsure if she is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.2.7"
msgid "Ñātikāya ñātikasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If she is related and he perceives her as related, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc13, pts-cs-bu-pc26.2.3, ms2V_587
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.3.2"
msgid "ñātikāya,"
msgstr "if she is related;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.3.3"
msgid "cīvaraṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he sews any requisite apart from a robe, or gets it sewn;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.3.4"
msgid "sikkhamānāya,"
msgstr "if it is a trainee nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.3.5"
msgid "sāmaṇeriyā,"
msgstr "if it is a novice nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.3.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.3.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_588
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc26:2.3.8"
msgid "Cīvarasibbanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The sixth rule, the training rule on sewing robes, is finished."
